          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Two variants different by execution sequence of the",
                " random and carbon background subtraction."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "1",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Variant A:",
                " On the first step the carbon background was removed",
                " by subtraction of the normalized CH2 spectrum. On the",
                " second step, the remaining random background with the",
                " exception the deuteron peak range was fitted by five",
                " order polynomial to provide adequate description the",
                " background in all energy range."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "2",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Variant B:",
                " After the background subtraction, the spectra both",
                " for the CD2 and CH2 targets were flat within the",
                " statistical errors and consistent with zero in the",
                " background range. On the next step the above CD2 and",
                " CH2 spectra were subtracted, and the d(g,p) reaction",
                " Emis spectra were obtained."
              ]
            }
          ],
